<br>
Luclin and Velious were all high hitpoint mobs with relatively high resists.  Planes of Power was low hitpoint mobs with high damage outputs.<br>
<br>
Theres no mixing, so all PoP encounters are largely the same, in as much as all Luclin and Velious encounters were the same.<br>
<br>
So what you end up with is one type of class (ranged damage dealers) being very useful all around for 10+ months, then another type of class (say melee) being useful for 10 months.  All that instead of mixing the encounters up a little, so that one day you may be doing one type of encounter, and the next day a totally different one.<br>
<br>
It's of course just my opinion, but it seems like the guilds transitioning between Luclin and PoP are mostly happy. Why? Because everyone has a use on at least some of the raids.  Instead you end up with the &quot;this is the caster expansion&quot; or &quot;this is the melee expansion.&quot;<br>
PoP is the &quot;Raid Expansion&quot; Lost Dungeons of Norrath is the &quot;Group Expansion&quot;<br>
<br>
From one extreme to the other. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loral>Loral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/03 6:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lost Dungeons of Norath</span><hr size=1> I wouldn't exactly call Xegony or Fennin Ro &quot;low hitpoint mobs&quot;. <p><a href="http://loralciriclight.com/"><img src="http://loralciriclight.com/images/loral_dragon_sig.jpg" border="0" alt="Loral's Signature" height="132" width="302"></a>
